// fix(audit): C1 — Supabase credentials redacted from committed file.
// This file MUST be kept local-only and is listed in .gitignore. However, it
// was tracked in a prior commit, so this sanitized content replaces the leaked
// values. Follow the steps below to restore a working local build.
//
// 1. Copy Supabase.xcconfig.example to Supabase.xcconfig and fill in real values
//    (or run: cp Supabase.xcconfig.example Supabase.xcconfig)
// 2. Populate SUPABASE_URL and SUPABASE_ANON_KEY from the Supabase dashboard
//    (Project Settings → API). Use the publishable `sb_publishable_*` key.
// 3. Run: git rm --cached iosApp/VitruvianPhoenix/Config/Supabase.xcconfig
//    from the Project-Phoenix-MP directory to stop git from tracking the file.
// 4. Rotate the compromised anon key in the Supabase dashboard
//    (Project Settings → API → Reset anon key).
// 5. The CI workflows in .github/workflows/ios-*.yml already write this file
//    from GitHub Actions secrets; no change to CI needed.
//
// The values below are intentional placeholders that will FAIL fast in
// PlatformModule.ios.kt require() checks so a developer notices immediately.

SUPABASE_URL = https:/$()/your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY = REPLACE_WITH_LOCAL_VALUE
